        id: 'eyJpdiI6IkV2ODFJVjE1UUZoUm5BVXdZdEs3WHc9PSIsInZhbHVlIjoieXp0eDdXNG9IMW5JSWdYMjEvRTQ0Zz09IiwibWFjIjoiNDMwMzEwMWRmZTQxZTlmNjI0ZTVhODI0MTNhYzE5MTlhNjE5ZjdhOTk4Nzg0NGNiYzk4Njc2YzQ5YjNkY2I3NiIsInRhZyI6IiJ9',
        title: 'Cost Accountant',
        slug: 'uwK6gn0ty4-cost-accountant',
        type: 8,
        type_name: ['Full time'],
        description:
          '\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJob Purpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ETo estimate production costs and track regular expenses, which may be related to a new process or a new product and recommend changes to pricing and business models through tracking data such as changing labor, supply costs, conducting market research.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuties and Responsibilities\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDevelops and maintains accurate costing systems in relation to labor, production methods and material supply.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAnalyzes changes in product design, raw materials, manufacturing methods, or services to determine effects on costs.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEstimates new and proposed product costs as well as product changes.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAnalyzes the data collected and logs a detailed record of the results.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPrepares (monthly, quarterly, and annual) cost forecasts.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAnalyzes monthly Cost of goods sold (CoGS), Purchase Price Variance (PPV) and Manufacturing variance journal entries.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAnalyzes data on material and labor costs to evaluate efficiency and effectiveness.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EReviews standard and actual costs for inaccuracies.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAnalyzes changes in product design, raw materials, manufacturing methods, or services provided to determine effects on costs.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAnalyzes actual costs and prepares periodic report comparing standard costs to actual costs and recommend cost efficiencies.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EProvides finance support on business cases; project cost calculations/quotations for strategic projects with appropriate labor and overhead rates and overall production costs (make/buy, outsourcing/insourcing).\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPrepares product cost reports which meet the needs of managers and other employees using the information.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EReconciles general ledger account balances for inventory, material expense and production costing items.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAssists cost related issues in Ad-Hoc projects to improve overall financial process and controls.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEvaluates and updates standard costs on a quarterly basis, which includes the review and analysis of material, direct &amp; indirect labor, and other overhead costs incurred.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EProvides input and recommendations for streamline processes and updates of the cost accounting policies and procedures.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EReviews and drives cost reductions, working capital opportunities and manufacturing productivity improvements.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPrepares the monthly cost of sales figures by analyzes expenses such as material, labor, research, and development expenses.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPerforms other duties assigned by the immediate supervisor\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E',
