                        title: 'Senior Budget Development Specialist',
                        slug: 'ei8ttuzE3P-senior-budget-development-specialist',
                        type: 8,
                        type_name: ['Full time'],
                        description:
                          '\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETEAM/PROGRAMME:&nbsp;Finance\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELOCATION:&nbsp; \u003C/strong\u003EAddis Ababa\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGRADE\u003C/strong\u003E:&nbsp; 1C\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPOST TYPE:&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003ENational&nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChild Safeguarding:&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELevel 3 -&nbsp;the responsibilities of the post may require the post holder to have regular contact with or access to children or young people\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EROLE PURPOSE:&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003EUnder supervision of Head of Budget Development\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003ES/he plays a key role in supporting Budget Team, the Senior Management including the Program Development Quality Director, Finance Director and New Business Development team in proposal development, thus contributing to the timely submission of high value and quality proposals to donors, by ensuring compliance of proposal budgets and related budget narrative to donor’s rules and regulations. S/he ensures that tools and templates are developed and used consistently for budget development sustainability and accurate cost recovery.&nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003ES/he will assist the Head of budgeting in coordinating and reviewing Master budget exercise, periodical forecasts, proposal budgeting &amp; review.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESCOPE OF ROLE:&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReports to:&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003EHead of Budgeting\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStaff directly reporting to this post: N/A\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKey Stakeholders:&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003EProgram Development Director; New Business Development Unit; Awards Unit; Program Development &amp; Quality technical teams; Program Operations; Humanitarian Team, Finance Department and Save the Children Member organization and Implementing Partners&nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIn line with SCI’s full spectrum programming, these key areas of accountability apply to SCI Ethiopia’s work in emergencies (acute and chronic) and in development settings.&nbsp;\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKey Role responsibility&nbsp; &nbsp;– Planning and Budgeting\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003EEnsure &amp; review proposal budgets reflect value for money and all cost that are included in the proposal budget are necessary and reflect our best estimate to deliver a project.&nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EResponsible to update and monitor use of tools such as Cost Allocation Methodology (CAM) to support full cost recovery for SCI.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ETo support his/her line manager to sensitize new initiative or policies that are introduced by the Centre or Regional Office to the budget development team.&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAssist his/ her line manager to lead high value budget related proposal development function&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003EEnsure proposal budget that come out from the unit is consistent with narrative and that the budget is tailored, reflecting relevance to and compliance with SCI and Donor requirements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESupports PDQ &amp; NBD team in the proposal development process for all proposals&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEnsures that information is provided in a timely fashion and relevant staff are involved in the proposal development process&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDisseminates donor and SCI standards to relevant personnel at the beginning of the process&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEnsures that a system is in place to analyse administrative costs and shared programme cost so that all aspects have been taken into account&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003EEnsures that all proposals, contracts and amendments with donors follow internal procedure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp style="text-align:justify;"\u003EAssist his/her line manager in the development and periodic revisions of the SCI Master Budget and annual/periodical projections of expenditures and funds in coordination with Awards, NBD team, PDQ and the rest of the finance team.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAs part of the country finance team assist annual planning process work closely with all departments and compile Country annual budgets forecast (Master budget)&nbsp;\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAssist Head of Budgeting in Coaching/ training new employees &amp; implementing partners by giving on job trainings\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPerform other related tasks and responsibilities assigned by Head of Budgeting\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKEY COMPETENCIES\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ELeading and Inspiring Others - accomplished\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDelivering Results – accomplished\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDeveloping Self and Others – leading edge\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EProblem Solving and Decision Making – leading edge\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EApplying Technical and Professional Expertise – accomplished\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EWorking Effectively with Others – accomplished\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ECommunicating with Impact - accomplished\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESKILLS AND BEHAVIOURS (our Values in Practice)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccountability:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHolds self-accountable for making decisions, managing resources efficiently, achieving and role modelling Save the Children values\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHolds the team and partners accountable to deliver on their responsibilities - giving them the freedom to deliver in the best way they see fit, providing the necessary development to improve performance and applying appropriate consequences when results are not achieved\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmbition:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESets ambitious and challenging goals for themselves (and their team), takes responsibility for their own personal development and encourages others to do the same\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EWidely shares their personal vision for Save the Children, engages and motivates others\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EFuture orientated, thinks strategically\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECollaboration:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EBuilds and maintains effective relationships, with their team, colleagues, members and external partners and supporters\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EValues diversity, sees it as a source of competitive strength\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EApproachable, good listener, easy to talk to\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreativity:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDevelops and encourages new and innovative solutions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EWilling to take disciplined risks\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntegrity:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHonest, encourages openness and transparency\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E',
